From Eric Hung Subject Re Adding a second IDE drive In article C r ur D Michael Cook writes I just bought a Western Digital Caviar MB IDE drive and I want to add it to my system which already has a WD IDE drive The controller says it supports hard drives, but when I plug in the cables, do the BIOS setup, and try to start the system, it pauses and then I get an invalid drive D error message The system boots, but I cannot access the new hard drive The new drive works fine as drive C if it's all alone, but I am not able to get both drives working at the same time Any help is appreciated Thanks, Mike You need to run FDISK Eric